examples.en: The jurors were unable to agree a verdict.
The jurors saw grisly photos of the crime scene.
One of the excused jurors planned to write a book.
Several jurors disbelieved the witness's testimony.
The defense attorney charged that the jurors were biased.
The jurors discussed the evidence and made their decision thereupon.
During their sequestration, jurors were not allowed to speak to reporters.
The judge instructed the jurors as to the points of law applicable in the case.
Baker had to convince jurors that his client had been nowhere near the scene of the murder.
They argued that the presence of TV cameras at the trial influenced the behavior of attorneys, witnesses, and jurors.
